reviews.review: Worth waiting for this all year, a must see for everyone!!

Incomprehensible storyline, flat and unsympathetic characters, and improbably plot devices make the film neither enjoyable nor a satisfactory ending to the so-called Star Wars sage.  Given what the fans were provided, the story should have ended with "Return of the Jedi" years ago.

Definitely the best of the 3 sequels.  I'd have made some other plot choices, but that in mind, JJ Abrams gave a Star Wars film worthy of the title.  Ignore the critics and enjoy the epic saga's conclusion.
Just enough fan service and nostalgia. The effects were brilliant and beautiful. Ive been a Star Wars fan since I was 7 years old and this was a completely satisfying conclusion.

JJ Abrams rescues the Star Wars legacy with this epic sendoff that also seriously course corrects the horrendous error that was The Last Jedi. It is a huge, masterful, breathless finale full of heart, tying together so much so well and still providing surprises. The only way JJ Abrams could have done better would have been to provide more background on Palpatine's resurrection. MINOR SPOILER!!! Darth Plagueis magic is hinted at, but that's it.
Great movie with an awesome ending!
Worst crawl, for the second best SW film, and 3rd best lightsaber fight ever.

This movie lacks the heart and soul of every other Star Wars film. JJ Abrams basically must have thought, "what do these idiots think they want?" And then made that movie, instead of having an original idea. This movie hurt my feelings as a Star Wars fan. They created lore in the universe to service just this one film and made several other characters completely irrelevant in the grand scheme of things to tie up loose ends. The pacing is poor, as is the editing and cinematography, and the writing for both the dialogue and plot is incoherent. If you really need to scratch a Star Wars itch, stay at home and watch The Mandalorian.

I personally loved this movie. I felt that there were definitely some "WTF?" moments, but overall it was exciting, fun, and provided closure. As a newer Star Wars fan, I have to say that the new trilogy was the reason I watched all the rest of the films and learned to appreciate the cultural impact of the films.

After the tragedy that was TLJ, Abrams is back in charge and completes the disaster. This is simply the worst Star Wars movie ever created and a total waste of time and money.

There is no real Plot. Charachters are forgettable and the twist ruins everything we know and love from the Star Wars Universe. Staring at an empty white wall is way more interesting than watching this movie.
